Interview-ready explanation

Cypress commands are asynchronous and queued. To access values from the DOM, we must use .then() or .invoke() because Cypress resolves commands later in the execution cycle.

Cypress aliases store resolved subjects and must be accessed using cy.get('@aliasName'). They cannot be used as selectors inside .find().




